  "text": "Contour interpolation using linear and nonlinear techniques is a well-researched topic. For biomedical image reconstruction, the intermediate contours may be generated using elastic interpolation technique [CITATION_1] . The initial and the final shapes are approximated using linear contour The major limitation of this approach is the linear approximation and interpolation of the intermediate contour and path, which misses intricate shape details. Also, the interpolation scheme is devoid of image intensity or any other shape specific features as exploited in the proposed approach.",
